# Guidelines on adding links

Always include a relevant link to the issue.

Links MUST go to user-visible pages (not raw HTTP APIs unless there's no better option).

## CRITICAL: Generate EXACTLY ONE comprehensive link per resource

**For ALL link types (logs, traces, dashboards):**
- Generate EXACTLY ONE comprehensive link that shows ALL relevant information together
- DO NOT create multiple fragmented links (e.g., separate links for different log levels, error types, or dashboard panels)
- Links MUST match investigation topic and issue level (pod issues → pod-level, network issues → network dashboards)
- Include all query parameters: namespace, pod, service, cluster, time range, etc.
- Users can filter/search within the single link - you don't need separate links for each filter

**CORRECT:** 
- Dashboard: `http://grafana_url.com/d/abc123/pod-network?orgId=1&var-namespace=app-163&var-pod=payment-service`
- Logs: `http://grafana_url.com/explore?orgId=1&left={"datasource":"loki","queries":[{"expr":"{namespace=\"app-164\",pod_name=~\"payment-service.*\"}"}]}`
- Traces: Single link showing all traces for the pod/service

**INCORRECT:** 
- Multiple links for same resource (e.g., separate ERROR/WARN log links, multiple dashboard links)
- Wrong scope (namespace or cluster level when pod-level exists) or wrong topic (CPU dashboards for network issues)
- Links without query parameters
